<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued June 23 at 4:28PM MDT until June 23 at 5:00PM MDT by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 500 PM MDT
FOR SOUTHWESTERN DANIELS...WEST CENTRAL ROOSEVELT AND EAST CENTRAL
VALLEY COUNTIES...
At 428 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 9 miles northeast of
Nashua, or 16 miles east of Glasgow, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Lustre and Volt.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
